The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Nov. 22: Mobile remittance services, which allow seamless and real-time fund transfer from one persons bank account to another through a mobile phone, was launched for the first time in India today. The Interbank Mobile Payment Service has seven banks, including the SBI, on board. The service has done wonders in other emerging market economies such as Kenya and the Philippines.                             
	 Mumbai, Nov. 22: Mahindra Satyam has announced a major rejig of its leadership team in the US to help expand its footprint in the country. Lakshmanan Chidambaram will head the banking and financial services, manufacturing, healthcare and life sciences verticals and BPO business of the firm in the US.                            
	 Mumbai, Nov. 22: Bharati Shipyard has proposed to acquire a 51 per cent stake and management control in south-based Tebma Shipyards for Rs 75.75 crore.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 22: Religare Capital Markets, the investment banking arm of Religare Enterprises, has acquired the UK operations of Barnard Jacobs Mellet for an estimated $40-50 million.                            
	 Calcutta, Nov. 22: Sharp Business Systems launched mobile handsets in the eastern region today.                                                                                                                          
